HEADWORD: artiodactyl
<hw>artiodactyl</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>placental mammal
having hooves with an even number of functional toes on each foot; a
member of the <er>artiodactyla</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> artiodactyle, even-toed ungulate, artiodactyl
mammal</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>artiodactyl</ent>⟦br⟧

